<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#2f2f4f">Originally posted by Ladas Sindarin on 08-09-2001 04:34 PM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">I don't completely understand the dissatisfaction with high end gear with lots of wisdom when it also has other needed stats, regardless of your current wisdom level.

Well, let me qualify that.  I do realize that there is a point of diminishing returns from wisdom post 200 compared to other stats, such as AC, HP, Mana and resists.

However, I see enough comments, many like the ones in this thread, lamenting the levels of their wisdom over 200 and commenting that they wish Verant would quit putting wisdom on top tier items.  Why?

Those same top tier items also tend to have high AC/HP/Sta/Resists, so all your bases are covered.  And even if each point of wisdom over 200 is only worth 1 mana, for those with 240+ wisdom, thats an extra 40 Mana.. and I see casters drool over items that add similiar amounts of raw mana.

Seems to me the title of this thread just translates to "Can't get rid of extra mana", and I was of the impression more mana is always good.  But then I play a ranger who just muddles through your boards, so please enlighten me.

[This message has been edited by Ladas Sindarin (edited 08-09-2001).]</TEXTAREA>
